	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["Lithium targets were made by rolling the metal,"
		,"lubricated with kerosene, between brass or polythene"
		,"sheets, and in this case no backing foil was"
		,"necessary. The latter method enabled uniform targets"
		,"of 0.001 inch thickness (1.4 mg/cm2) to be produced."
		,"The targets were hung in the beam and stretched by a"
		,"small weight suspended from them."]
	}
